post.data1: Give me a lever long enough and a fulcrum on which to place it, and I shall move the world.
post.author: Archimedes

post.data1: The shortest distance between two points is a straight line.
post.author: Archimedes

post.data1: There is no hunting like the hunting of man, and those who have hunted armed men long enough and liked it, never care for anything else thereafter.
post.author: Ernest Hemingway

post.data1: Do not dwell in the past, do not dream of the future, and concentrate the mind on the present moment.
post.author: Buddha

post.data1: A woman of the world is anxious to exhibit her form and shape, whether walking, standing, sitting, or sleeping. Even when represented as a picture, she desires to captivate with the charms of her beauty and, thus, rob men of their steadfast hearts.
post.author: Buddha
